INSERT OR IGNORE INTO `lessons` (`id`,`course_id`,`title`,`section_id`,`lesson_type`,`content`,`content_format`,`video_key`,`primary_asset_id`,`intro_asset_id`,`duration_minutes`,`is_preview`,`available_after_days`,`required_watch_percent`,`transcript`,`experience_json`,`position`,`updated_at`) SELECT 'cmf-module-2-24-lesson-09','cognizen-crypto-mastery-foundations-production','Module Summary and Key Takeaway','cmf-module-2-24','text','## Your outcome

Explain the key ideas in Module Summary and Key Takeaway, distinguish evidence from assumption, and apply them to a practical digital-asset decision.

### Module Summary

Decentralised finance uses blockchains and smart contracts to provide financial services involving:

Trading

Lending

Borrowing

Staking

Liquidity

Stablecoins

Derivatives

Asset management

Governance

Users commonly interact through self-custodial wallets.

DeFi can provide:

Permissionless access

Transparency

Programmability

Continuous operation

Composability

These benefits also create greater individual responsibility.

DeFi does not eliminate trust.

It relocates trust into:

Smart contract code

Blockchain security

Oracles

Governance

Administrator controls

Stablecoins

User wallets

Yields may come from borrower interest, trading fees, network issuance, protocol revenue or incentive tokens.

The source and sustainability of the yield must be evaluated.

Major risks include:

Smart contract exploits

Liquidation

Stablecoin failure

Oracle manipulation

Governance capture

Bridge failure

Front-end attacks

Malicious approvals

Network congestion

Regulatory uncertainty

Composability can multiply both innovation and risk.

A position using several protocols may contain many interconnected failure points.

Responsible participation requires understanding the complete transaction, limiting position size, testing withdrawals, managing approvals and preparing for the possibility of total loss.

### Key Takeaway

DeFi can make financial services open, programmable and globally accessible.

It can also combine smart contracts, volatile collateral, oracles, governance systems, bridges and user-controlled wallets into one complex chain of risk.

Do not judge a DeFi opportunity by its advertised yield.

Understand the complete system, identify every dependency and expose only capital that can survive the failure of any one layer.','markdown',NULL,NULL,NULL,2,0,0,0,'','',9,1785297600000 WHERE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM `courses` WHERE `id`='cognizen-crypto-mastery-foundations-production');
